  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of access to safe water and sanitation facilities to IDP and host communities in Hamdaniya and Hamam Al Alil areas affected by Mosul offensive</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through the proposed action PIN aims to assist populations affected by the Mosul military offensive through provision of access to safe water and sanitation facilities. Up to an estimated 1.2-1.5 million individuals are expected to be affected by fighting and human rights abuses in and around Mosul, and are forced toflee and seek safety in camps/collective shelters/abandoned buildings. The project activities will target host community, returnee and IDP families living in newly retaken areas in Hamdaniya and Hamam Al Alil districts (Ninewa governorate) in villages with limited access to water. Access to sustained and equitable water will be provided by the rehabilitation of 1 compact unit in Hamam Al Alil (Egnetra WTP - identified by DoW as currently the biggest priority) and 1 in Hamdaniya (Balawat) district and by the rehabilitation of water and sanitation facilities in 5 schools in Hamdaniya district (2 schools in Tal Akub, Al Numaniya, Musherfa and Al Khidir). Although the locations for intervention were already identified and chosen based on assessments and PIN&#x2019;s current presence in the areas, PIN strives  to maintain a flexible approach with the opportunity to  shift to other locations in case of more urgent identified needs and gaps.
All proposed actions - rehabilitation of water treatment plants and compact units as well as WASH response in schools were identified as major needs by WASH cluster. Focusing on CU will ensure a sustainable access to water for host, returnee and IDP communities. The rehabilitation of water and sanitation conditions of schools will significantly improve the safety and dignity of learning spaces for boys and girls, especially those with disabilities, who currently do not have equal access to water and sanitation facilities at schools
The project activities will be closely coordinated with the WASH Cluster, especially the WASH Cluster Water Treatment Plant Working Group in Erbil, the Department of Water in Ninewa and Hamam Al Alil and other actors operating in targeted areas.</narrative>
  </description>
